James W. Breyer (born July 1961)[2] is an American venture capitalist, founder and CEO of Breyer Capital, an investment and venture philanthropy firm, and a partner at Accel Partners, a venture capital firm. Breyer has invested in over 30 companies that have gone public or completed a merger,[3] with some of these investments, including Facebook,[4] earning over 100 times cost and many others over 25 times cost.[5] On the Forbes 2016 list of the world's billionaires, he was ranked #722 with a net worth of US$2.4 billion.[1]



