James W. Breyer  Founder and Chief Executive Officer, Breyer CapitalAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 18 Board Members in 18 different organizations across 28 different industries.See Board Relationships56--
Background

		Mr. James W. Breyer, also known as Jim, founded Breyer Capital in 2006 and serves as Chief Executive Officer since July 2006. He serves as a Founding Insight Partner at Technology Crossover Investors. Mr. Breyer serves as a Co-Founder of AKKR and also served on its Board. He serves a Co-Founder at the IDG-Accel China Funds and serves as its Partner. Mr. Breyer serves as an Honorary Professor of the Yuelu Academy, Hunan University since December 2005. He served as President ... of Western Association of Venture Capitalists. Mr. Breyer served as a Co-Founder, President, Managing General Partner and General Partner since 1990 at Accel. He served as a Partner since 1987 till April 2016 at Accel. He also served in product marketing and management at Hearme, Hewlett-Packard Company and Apple Inc. Mr. Breyer served as a Trustee at Menlo School. He served as a Management Consultant at McKinsey & Company, Inc. Mr. Breyer serves as a Director of Stanford Technology Ventures Program and Circle. He has been an Independent Director of Blackstone Group Management L.L.C at The Blackstone Group L.P. since July 14, 2016. Mr. Breyer serves as a Director of Circle Internet Financial, Inc., since October 31, 2013. He serves as an Independent Director of Twenty-First Century Fox, Inc. since October 21, 2011 and NWS since October 2011. Mr. Breyer serves as a Director of Woven, Inc., Vostu USA Inc., Cybermeals Inc., Legend Picturesen, LLC, eMac Digital, Global Grind, Motive Communication and CircleOne Holdings. He serves as a Director of Wickr Inc. Mr. Breyer is a Trustee of the Metropolitan Museum of Art and San Francisco Museum of Modern Art. Mr. Breyer serves as a Member of Advisory Board of School of Economics & Management Tsing Hua University and IDG Capital Partners. He serves as a Director of the Associates of Technet. Mr. Breyer serves as a member of the Advisory Board of Stanford University School of Engineering and also on the Advisory Board of the Tsinghua University School of Economics and Management in Beijing. He serves on the Board of the Associates of Harvard Business School, The Boston Celtics, Epicenter and Silicon Valley Community Ventures. Mr. Breyer serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Council on Foreign Relations, The President and Fellows of Harvard College and Metropolitan Museum of Art. He serves as a Member of Fiduciary Oversight Board since July 1, 2013. Mr. Breyer served as Lead Director/Presiding Director and Independent Director at Wal-Mart Stores Inc. from June 1, 2006 to June 2013 and from 2001 to 2013 respectively. He served as the Chairman of National Venture Capital Association. Mr. Breyer served as a Director of Brightcove, Inc. from 2004 to January 30, 2013, Etsy, Inc. since January 2008 until June 9, 2016, Marvel Entertainment, LLC from June 2006 to December 31, 2009, RealNetworks Inc. from October 1995 to June 3, 2008 and Prosper Marketplace, Inc. from April 2005 to June 19, 2012. He served as a Director of News Corp. since October 2011 and Vostu, Ltd. Mr. Breyer served as a Director/Board Observer of RockMelt, Inc. He served as a Director of Facebook, Inc. from April 2005 to June 11, 2013 and Model N, Inc. from June 2000 to 2013. He was a Director of Legendary Entertainment. Mr. Breyer served as an Independent Director of Dell Inc. from April 2009 to October 17, 2013. He was elected a fellow of the Harvard Corporation, Harvard University's senior governing board In February, 2013. Mr. Breyer served as a Director of GeoComm Systems, Groove Networks, Inc., AlphaBlox Corporation Inc., Andale, Inc., Savista LLC, Family Wonder, Inc., Maven Networks, Inc., Apexon, Inc., Lightspan, Inc., IBM Kenexa BrassRing Inc., and Datasweep, Inc. He served as the Chairman of Harvard Business School California Research Center. Mr. Breyer served as a Director of Raytheon BBN Technologies Corp., DataLogix Holdings, Inc, GG Digital, Inc, Booyah, Inc. since May 2010 and Ubermedia, Inc. since February 14, 2011. Mr. Breyer served as a Member of Advisory Board and Director at Pacific Community Ventures. He served as a Member of Advisory Board of Mode Media Corporation. Mr. Breyer has experience as an investor in over 30 consumer internet, media and technology companies. He has received the IBF Special Achievement Award for career contributions to the venture capital industry. Mr. Breyer was ranked #1 on Forbes Midas List of top technology investors multiple times. Fortune also named Mr. Breyer the smartest investor in technology and one of the ten smartest people in the technology industry. He was named to the New Establishment Hall of Fame by vanity fair and he received the Silicon Valley Lifetime Visionary Award. Mr. Breyer is passionate about investing, social entrepreneurship and venture philanthropy and actively supports numerous educational and environmental non-profit initiatives. He is a fellow of the Harvard Corporation In February, 2013. Mr. Breyer holds an M.B.A. from Harvard Business School, where he was named a George Baker Scholar in 1987 and a B.S. in Interdisciplinary Studies with highest distinction from Stanford University in 1983.Read Full Background




