Facebook



Facebook’s mission is to give people the power to share and make the world more open and connected. Jim Breyer led the first institutional venture capital round in Facebook in April 2005 and joined the board. 
 




Legendary



Legendary is a leading media and data analytics company with films including the Dark Knight series, Jurassic World, and Interstellar. Jim Breyer is the lead investor/board member.

"Thomas Tull is an exceptional entrepreneur: he faces the future with excitement, creativity, and courage." - Jim Breyer 2010
 




Kensho



Kensho is the next-generation analytics and knowledge platform for investment professionals. It is pioneering real-time statistical computing systems and scalable analytics architectures.
 




Lyra Health



Founded by former Facebook executive David Ebersman, Lyra Health is transforming mental health care through technology. Its mission is to get more patients the care they need when they need it. 
 




Oscar Health



Oscar Health makes health insurance simple, intuitive, and human through technology, data, and design. Its goal is to have the happiest members paying the lowest costs for the healthiest outcome.  
 




IDG Capital Partners



IDG China Capital is a pioneer venture capital investor in China. The investment firm concentrates on technology, media, and telecom investments.  IDG has invested in a number of outstanding Chinese companies, including the series A rounds of Tencent and Baidu. Breyer Capital is the US partner and sponsor of IDG China Capital.  
 




Etsy



Etsy is an innovative e-commerce marketplace where people around the world connect to buy and sell unique goods. Jim Breyer led a major early venture round in 2008 and joined the board. 
 




DRIVETRIBE



DRIVETRIBE is a next-generation digital media platform dedicated to motoring and adventure founded by former Top Gear stars Jeremy Clarkson, Richard Hammond and James May.  

“DRIVETRIBE is rooted in an incredibly forward-thinking approach to both content creation and consumption: one that recognizes the importance of artificial intelligence in facilitating real audience engagement.” - Jim Breyer 2016
 




AKKR



A private equity firm providing growth capital to the emerging leaders of the technology world with over $4 billion in assets under management. AKKR was founded in 2000 and Jim Breyer has remained active since its founding. 
 




Circle



Circle was founded by Jeremy Allaire in 2013. Its money applications and platform technologies make it easy to exchange, store, send, and receive money over the blockchain. Jim Breyer invested in the A round and joined the board.
"I'm proud to be working with Jeremy for the third time." Jim Breyer 2013
 




Marvel



